    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1971-01-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1971-01-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="134"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d134">
                <head>134. Memorandum From the Executive Secretary of the Department of State
                        (<persName type="from">Eliot</persName>) to the Assistant Secretary of State
                    for European Affairs (<persName corresp="#p_HMJA1" type="to"
                        >Hillenbrand</persName>)<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d134fn1">Source:
                        National Archives, <gloss target="#t_RG1">RG</gloss> 59, <gloss
                            target="#t_SS1">S/S</gloss> Memoranda Files: Lots 72 D 371, Memos, 1971,
                        Vol. 3. Secret. Copies were sent to <persName corresp="#p_RWP1"
                            >Rogers</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_IJNII1">Irwin</persName>,
                            <persName corresp="#p_JUA1">Johnson</persName>, <persName
                            corresp="#p_PRF3">Pedersen</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_SJR2"
                            >Stevenson</persName>, the heads of 10 bureaus, and the Director of
                            <gloss target="#t_ACDA1">ACDA</gloss>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1971-01-18">January 18, 1971</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Coordination of Official Contacts with the <gloss target="#t_USSR1"
                            >USSR</gloss>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <p>Upon reading Mr. <persName corresp="#p_KHA1">Kissinger</persName>’s memorandum of
                    January 7 on the above subject,<note n="2" xml:id="d134fn2">
                        <ref target="#d131">Document 131.</ref>
                    </note> the Secretary asked me to inform you that the procedures outlined in the
                    memorandum should not alter our internal procedures for clearances of
                    substantive cables with the White House. This means that such cables will only
                    be cleared with the White House if the Secretary, the Under Secretary, or the
                    Under Secretary for Political Affairs deem it necessary.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_ETLJ2">Theodore L. Eliot Jr.</persName>
                        <note n="3" xml:id="d134fn3">Printed from a copy that indicates Eliot signed
                            the original.</note>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
